caption: The food is always good and fresh. Great customer service

Great place to grab Vietnamese and other asian snacks. The fried tofu is amazing. Love the lemongrass tofu and the black fungus fried tofu is amazing. Have to hit this place every time we are over on Jimmy Carter. Also very clean and stylish since the recent makeover. Must visit.

Been going for years. Love the tofu selections and bánh mì dac biet. This is the first time I've been back since pandemic started. They have remodeled and looks sleeker, servings of tofu served behind counters and everyone was wearing masks. I'll be back the next time I'm in town!
Fast and covid friendly.  A hidden gem for fast food- snacks, meals, desserts and drinks
Hidden gem with a bounty of Viet take-out foods. The selection can be overwhelming in a good way.

Best fresh banh mi in town and their prices are $4 per sandwich and they have the “buy 5 get the 6th free.” This store specializes in freshly made Vietnamese entrees and treats. We always get their soy milk which is fresh as well! The black top soy milk is sugar free and the orange top is with sugar. I always make the drive just to get my parents everything here, located in the shopping center near Great Wall make sure to stop by and try some stuff!

The best selection of any Vietnamese deli I've seen in Atlanta, or any other city for that matter.  Deli is cleaner and more presentable than most, and the customer service was actually decent. It gets busy, so I suggest going during off hours.  Prices were as expected for a Vietnamese deli: cheap!  Out of the 5 or so Vietnamese delis I've been to in Atlanta, this is easily my favorite.  UPDATE: Sandwiches have amazing bread.  (Side note: There is a rash of falsified 1-star reviews if you scroll down.  Not sure if they're connected to competition or are just whiners.)

Come here to grab something for our breakfast but end up buying a lot of food for lunch and dinner. Super clean and with reasonable price.  Great amount of choices you can bring to your road trip to the great smoky mountain or blue ridge road.  The soft tofu was awesome! So smooth and lightly sweet if you don't mix it with the ginger syrup. The combination Spring roll is a must. Four is only around 4 bucks. The banana cake with coconut cream was a good choice for snack which was not too sweet.

I used to love this place. First time I had bahn mi it was here. They used to be accommodating. Sold meat by the pound and all the fixings so I could grab fresh veggies at the farmers market in the same complex go home and fix fresh sandwiches for a party. No longer, ...in fact the last 3 times I was in they had sold out of sandwhiches entirely and all 3 times were right around 6 pm. It is simply poor planning also, the food in their hot tray is always cold. Don't waste your time. There are many bahn mi options in this area with more flavorful items and friendlier staff.

The sign says (or maybe it used to say) √n Tofu.  I loved the sign, and it always made me wonder what the square root of N was. It might mean that if N is 16 you will get 4 Tofu.  It could also mean that the square root of Tofu is the soy bean.  Either way, the food is great, and you will want to eat more than 4 Tofu, and more than 4 Soy beans.  I have always loved this place, and I didn't think it could get any better, but it did... The renovations are great.  It feels super clean now, and the store is organized really well.  The variety of food has remained, and the great taste is still there too.  I gladly give it √n stars - where N = 25!
This is a great place to pick up some authentic Asian cuisines. I’ve been buying food from here for many years. Highly recommended.

I’ve been coming here for years with my boyfriend and his family and have always loved the food. They recently renovated, and the inside looks great and I love the efficiency of going through the line to order now. However, last week we came to get banh mi, and when we got home, I noticed that all of our banh mi thit nuong had peanuts in it. I’m not sure if the recipe has changed since the renovation but for years now, there weren’t peanuts in this sandwich. My boyfriend happens to have a peanut allergy, but luckily, we noticed the peanuts before he ate any of the banh mi. Since this is the first time this has ever happened, I’m sure it was an accident. But I hope that either the cooks at VN Tofu can be a little more careful in the future when preparing the sandwiches to avoid adding unwanted peanuts to people’s food or if this is the new recipe, that management could advertise that there are going to be peanuts in the food for customers’ safety.

There's also a station near the cash register where they'll make you a variety of banh mi (sandwiches). I definitely come here to stock up on snacks and whenever I"m too lazy to cook.

VN Tofu is tucked away in a very busy shopping center. Parking is difficult but if you don't mind walking then there's plenty of spots towards the back. I love going to VN for the various snacks and banh mi! Over the years it's always been a great experience. The egg rolls are great and so are the spring rolls. I also love their desserts and I always leave with atleast 3-5 packages of Nam. I've honestly never had a complaint until recently.  The past few times I've visited I've been very disappointed in the quality of the food. One of the desserts I had was definitely spoiled and had a dead fly on the outside bottom of the cup. The price for the nam I get went up ridiculously and the fried bananas were more oil than banana. But the most upsetting thing for me is the banh mi. I always get the combination and lately it's been awful. Little to no meat, super dry and the bread is chewy. I've also had a bad experience with one employee where she was extremely rude to my fiance and ignored him as he tried to speak to her.  I love the convenience of the store I just wish the quality would improve. I'll be back but much less than usual unless I see some improvements.
